ucts.</description><dc:creator>Tripp Mickle</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 18:06:09 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cloud computing</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer Chip</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/04/24/business/24biz-google-anthropic-1/24biz-google-anthropic-1-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Gabby Jones/Bloomberg</media:credit><media:description>Google investment in Anthropic tightens the companies’ relationship even as they compete in some areas.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>